hopobject.body: Do you know the number for ? healthwithus.com Some had hoped Maspero would be a turning point for the country, but instead it’s become yet another scar on a revolution waged to make Egypt more equitable than it had been under three decades of Mubarak’s repressive rule. Instead, accountability has fallen by the wayside and facts are hard to come by, especially in a one-road village more than 150 miles from the bustling capital.
